  "text": "To examine the vertical structure of the changes in temperature and winds, Fig. 8 shows a cross section of the 1950-1976 mean JJA temperature (contours) and vector winds along 105°-122°E (the same longitudes for the PDI) from the NCEP/NCAR reanalyses and the AM2.1 GOGA runs (Fig. 8a, b) , along with their decadal changes (Fig. 8c,  d ) and the changes from the CAM3 GOGA and TOGA runs (Fig. 8e, f) . The NCEP/NCAR reanalyses shows relatively warm air and corresponding upward motion over Southeast Asia (*10°-30°N) (Fig. 8a) , with weak upward motion north of *40°N. The AM2.1 model roughly reproduces this broad feature, with the strongest upward motion shifted southward. The changes from the reanalyses (Fig. 8c) show cooling over the land (north of *25°N) and warming over the ocean (south of *25°N) during 1977-2000 relative to 1950-1976 . Accompanying this change in land-ocean temperature gradients, anomalous descending and ascending motion occurs over the northern land and southern ocean areas, respectively, with anomalous northerly winds between 20°and 50°N (Fig. 8c) . The strongest cooling center is around the 300 hPa level. showed that this cooling center can enhance the southern part of the high level jet stream and weaken the northern part of the high level jet stream through the geostrophic balance, resulting in the southward shift of high level jet while enhancing anomalous low-level northerlies on the southeastern part of the cooling center [CITATION_1] . In summary, the temperature and associated circulation changes shown in Fig. 8c are consistent with a weakened EASM (i.e., weaker southerly winds over East China, cf. Fig. 1e, f) .",
